Tournament format

Group Stage: two groups, each team plays against all other teams in their group.
The best 2 teams from each group advance to the Playoffs:

– Semi-finals: 1st team from one group vs 2nd team from another group
– Match for the bronze medals
– Grand Final

All matches are 5 vs 5 duels in a best-of-3 format.

tournaments.about:
🌍 TECS - Torneo por Equipos Carcassonne Spain


Inspired by the amazing CTCB (Torneio de Times Carcassonne Brasil), Spain is launching its first team-based Carcassonne tournament: TECS (Torneo por Equipos Carcassonne Spain)!


💥 Teams of 4 to 6 players will compete each week in head-to-head matchups. Each matchup will consist of 3 duels (1v1), making it a more accessible format than the WTCOC's usual 5-player structure.


🗓 The tournament starts the week of August 18th, with weekly group stage matchups leading to a knockout final phase.


🇪🇸 The tournament is intended for Spanish players or residents in Spain, but each team is allowed one international player.
If you see a team looking for players in the list and you'd like to join them — or if you know a Spanish player you'd love to team up with — this is your chance to reach out!


By registering as an international player, you’re simply declaring your availability to join a team. Your name will appear in a public list that captains and other players can use to contact you if they’re looking for someone.


📅 Registration deadline: August 10th


📝 International Player Sign-Up Form (for those without a team yet):
https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSezfB-TvmG0s4bxW47pQJaCm5sK17eR-KSoWKUfIJGUbdBP3w/viewform?usp=dialog


👥 Team & Player Availability List:
https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/u/5/d/e/2PACX-1vTzpjHukUOCCL2u0AtUXnApAVjqbWqoZ4NEIdasxJ8yic3mSKF7z8XzAFI79wW4zj6RgV2PQ5TC9a9T/pubhtml

tournaments.about:
The Belarusian Carcassonne Premier League (BCPL) is an online competition for the Carcassonne board game played in real time.

Only Belarusian players are allowed to participate in the tournament.

All games take place on the platform https://boardgamearena.com/

Players compete in a one-on-one round-robin format until two wins (best of 3).

The winners qualify for the offline Championship of Belarus in Carcassonne.
